# __PKG_NAME__

A minimal [BigConfig](https://www.bigconfig.ai) package, scaffolded from the
`create-ts-bigconfig-package` skill. It depends on the BigConfig TypeScript SDK
(`big-config`) and renders one template through a single `hello` stage.

## Commands

```bash
npm install
npm run build        # tsc -> dist/
npm run typecheck
npm test
npm run __PKG_NAME__ -- help              # run the CLI from source via tsx
npm run __PKG_NAME__ -- package validate
npm run __PKG_NAME__ -- package build
node run package build                     # run through the launcher-friendly entry point
```

## Layout

```
__PKG_NAME__/
├── run                       # launcher entry point (copied by bc-pkg; safe defaults only)
├── package.json              # one root manifest; ships dist/src + src/resources
├── src/
│   ├── cli.ts                # main(argv, opts) dispatcher
│   ├── __PKG_NAME__/
│   │   ├── options.ts        # profiles + active profile (`bb`)
│   │   ├── params.ts         # BC_PAR_* overrides -> opts
│   │   ├── tools.ts          # the `hello` render stage
│   │   ├── validation.ts     # pure validate report + workflow step
│   │   ├── package.ts        # validate/build verbs + __PKG_VAR__Star wrapper
│   │   └── interop.ts        # alias <-> namespaced-key bridge
│   └── resources/__PKG_NS_PATH__/tools/hello/greeting.txt
└── test/
```

## Grow it

- Add params to the profile in `options.ts` (and the `DEFAULT_PROFILE` in `run`),
  keeping keys kebab-case to match template variables.
- Add a stage: write a render function in `tools.ts`, `registerWorkflow` it, and add
  it to the `build` (and any `create`/`delete`) pipeline in `package.ts`.
- Override any param at runtime with `BC_PAR_*` env vars (e.g. `BC_PAR_NAME=alice`).
- Generated output lands in `.dist/` — never edit it as source.
